					<head>Perush</head>
					<msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80008475" rend="visible">
						<summary>An Arabic commentary on the second book of Samuel by Yitsḥaḳ  ben Shemuʾel ha-Sefardi.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he">Judeo-Arabic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80008475">
							<title xml:lang="en">Commentary on the book of Samuel</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פירוש על שמואל </title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush ʿal sefer Shemuʾel </title>
							<locus from="1r" to="193v"/>
							<note>
								<p>The Arabic translation, generally in small sections, precedes the respective portions of the commentary. Only the first words of the Hebrew text are given.</p>
								<p>Contains numerous references to the early grammarians and commentators: Saʿadyah Gaʾon (<locus n="134v, 164v, 169v"/>),  Sherira Gaʾon (<locus n="42r, 42v"/>), Hai Gaʾon (<locus n="33r, 158v, 162r"/>),  Abu Zakariya Yaḥya (<locus n="11r, 17r, 29r,150r, 156v, 163r"/>), Abu 'l-Walid Merwan ibn Jannaḥ (<locus n="2r, 6r, 15v, 120v"/>), Yehudah ibn Balaʿam (<locus n="32v, 33r, 33v"/>), Mosheh ben Shemuʾel ibn Giḳaṭila (<locus n="108v, 150v"/>),  Natan ben Yeḥiel (<locus n="95v, 106r"/>), Abu ʾAli al-Baṣrī (<locus n="164v"/>), and also to several anonymous commentaries, general works of reference, and to his own works.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Yitsḥaḳ  ben Shemuʾel ha-Sefardi</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">יצחק בן שמואל הספרדי</persName>
							</author>
							<filiation>Similar to a Genizah fragment from Cambridge, 1a 25, in terms of script. See also <ref target="Neubauer_1891" type="number">455</ref> .</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; Oriental semi-cursive script of 14-15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>193 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>250</height>
